description:
"APOCALYPSE WARS" CONTINUES!

The ALL-NEW X-MEN's entry into "APOCALYPSE WARS" starts here! The ALL-NEW X-MEN are on a mission to step out of the shadows of their predecessors and write their own futures. And none are more determined to forge their own way than Evan Sabahnur, who is allegedly destined to one day become the genocidal villain APOCALYPSE. But now, by way of an unintentional intervention by his teammate Beast, Evan is brought face-to-face with Apocalypse himself...and also brought face-to-face with the question he's been running from: Can you escape your destiny?

The Marvel Masterworks once again presents Captain Marvel -- and this volume completes his adventures! From the epic Battle of Titan to the all-time classic Death of Captain Marvel, you can now experience every page of Mar-Vell's cosmic quest in painstakingly restored hardcover editions. The action begins with a plan set in motion by Thanos's death: the worldwide computer ISAAC has taken control of Titan in Thanos's name! To overcome this deadly threat, Captain Marvel and Drax the Destroyer must fight a war on two fronts that spans the entire solar system. Art turns by Steve Ditko and Frank Miller, plus a rare tale held over for years, set the stage for Jim Starlin's touching farewell to Mar-Vell. description:
THE HUNT FOR BLACK OCTOBER STARTS NOW!

Venom's made a solid go as newly-recruited Agent of the Cosmos, aiding the hopeless and oppressed across the galaxy. He's even picked up some powerful and powefully odd allies (sad cyborg 803, strong serpent-tressed Iqa, and MERCENARY SPACE PANDA Pik Rollo). But even they might not be enough to stop what's coming. A fearsome new foe has set sights on Agents of the Cosmos, so it looks like Venom's training is about to get INTENSIVE.

A NEW STORY STARTS NOW!

Once upon a time a robot and a witch fell in love. What followed was a tale of the dead and the dying, of the hopeful and the lost, of the wronged and the avenged. And in the end, after both had fallen, the witch and the robot rose from their dirt and eyed each other across a field of blood and bone.

Forty-five years in the making, this is the story of Scarlet Witch and the Vision. Before family, there was love. And war.

description: Your favorite web-slinging wonders from SPIDER-VERSE, together on one titanic team! But when Electro and his own army of alternate-reality evildoers wreak havoc across the Web of Life, it will take the whole team - plus some amazing Spider-guests - to stop him! Gwen finds herself stranded far from home, but the breakout star of SPIDER-VERSE is no damsel in distress. Can she find her way back to the fight in time, before things go from bad to Electroverse? They're the Web-Warriors, and their not-so-friendly neighborhood is all of reality! Collecting WEB WARRIORS #1-5 and material from AMAZING SPIDER-MAN (2015) #1.

But from Asteroid M to Weapon X, Marvel's mightiest mutants are getting brainwashed wherever they go! Featuring mysteries from Wolverine's history and the first flashback appearance of Team X - plus Acolytes, ninjas and more! Omega Red! Maverick! Sabretooth! And the debut of the classic Blue and Gold X-Men teams! It's the opening issues of 1991's blockbuster "adjectiveless" X-MEN series like you've never seen them before - remastered and fully recolored in modern style! Collecting X-MEN (1991) #1-7.

Celebrate the 75th anniversary of Archie Comics with this special retrospective presentation! Stepping out of Archie's shadow, Betty & Veronica finally got their chance to shine in the spotlight with their own title in 1950. For over 600 issues spanning across two volumes, these two BFFs proved that, with or without Archie, their stories were always interesting, hilarious and unforgettable -- and their fashion was always top-notch! On the eve of the upcoming third volume of Betty & Veronica, we'll take a look back at some of the stories that made their lasting imprint on America for over 60 years. Archie may never know the answer, but you can finally decide: Betty or Veronica?

description: In part 2 of "The Ballad of Barnacle Bill," SpongeBob and the ocean's saltiest sailor, Barnacle Bill, take on the deadly denizens of Rough 'n' Tough Reef-lowlife pirate scum, the sinister White Water Witch, a giant Fish Roc, and the belligerent bully Gangplank Gus! It's a thimbleful of thrilling theater with the excitement of an exploding Segar! Plus: facts about hungry shipworms by Maris Wicks! Gary fights Plankton, by James Kochalka and Hilary Barta! And more!
name: The Ballad of Barnacle Bill Part 2

description:
The Fall of Deadworld gathers pace as Fairfax battles against the tide of the Dark Judges – will he survive and is there anything he can do to alter the fate of his world? Also in this week’s Prog: Judge Dredd: The Lion's Den by Michael Carroll, PJ Holden, Adam Brown, and Annie Parkhouse; Survival Geeks: Lord of the Ringers by Gordon Rennie, Emma Beeby, Neil Googe, Gary Caldwell, and Ellie De Ville; Tainted: The Fall of Deadworld by Kek-W, Dave Kendall, and Annie Parkhouse; Brink by Dan Abnett, INJ Culbard, and Simon Bowland; and Sláine: Psychopomp by Pat Mills, Simon Davis, and Ellie De Ville.

Tensions are running high in the Assassin Cell as Charlotte's investigation is plagued by the limitations of the portable Animus. When she turns on Kody, Galina leaps to defend him. With tempers at breaking point, can the team pull themselves back together before they are torn apart for good?

On the mysterious Isle with No Name, Takeo has finally found his long lost brother, Akio, but before he can get the answers he so desperately needs, he must fight a duel with Shobei, an unbeatable Samurai who longs only to join his dead wife and daughter in the after-life.

description: The conspiracy that gripped fans for nine seasons is finally laid bare! Just who are the shadowy syndicate? What really happened to Mulder's sister? And is the Earth truly going to be colonized by extra-terrestrials? All these questions and more are answered in this unmissable collection featuring interviews with show creator Chris Carter, the duplicitous "Mr. X" - Steven Williams - the Lone Gunmen, the iconic William B. Davis (aka the Cigarette Smoking Man), plus many, many more. From cloning to alien abduction, the truth that almost cost agents Mulder and Scully their lives will finally be revealed.
name: Conspiracy Theory - The Truth, Secrets & Lies

description: An engrossing universe awaits the reader who dares go past the first page of this off kilter gothic saga, populated with a rich assortment of bizarre characters and haunting plots. Hints of Lovecraft and Poe abound as hidden secrets, the occult, succubi, spiritual séances, and repressed urges are interwoven in Frédéric Bézian's award-winning literary and spectacularly dark fantasy.
name: HC

description: The life of Agatha Christie was as mysterious and eventful as her fiction. This beautifully illustrated graphic novel traces the life of the Queen of Whodunnit from her childhood in Torquay, England, through a career filled with success, mischief, and adventure, to her later years as Dame Agatha. Revealing a side to Christie that will surprise and delight many readers, Agatha introduces us to a free-spirited and thoroughly modern woman who, among other things, enjoyed flying, travel, and surfing. Centering around an episode in 1926 when Christie staged her own disappearance, Agatha is an intriguing, entertaining, and funny exploration of the 20th century's best-loved crime novelist.
name: GN

volume.name: Agatha: The Real Life of Agatha Christie

description: Alan is just a bodyguard trying to make a living. But this is the future, and to survive Alan Dracon must deal with high-tech industrial moguls, genetically modified organisms... and seductive corporates. And most of them want him dead. Action and adventure in the not-so-near future brought to you by Stefano Martino (George R.R. Martin's Doorways, Doctor Who).
The war both home and abroad. The struggle between man and monster. The epic fight between good and evil. All of these battles and more waging within the soul of one man...and all in one small town.
name: We Bury Our Dread

description: Renegade Arts' first anthology. Tales of myth, adventure and humor told at the top of the world. Written and drawn by Inuit and Northern Canadian creators.
name: HC

description: In Munch, writer and artist Steffen Kverneland brings the story of one of the world's most influential painters to vivid life. This extraordinary, inventive graphic novel uses text drawn exclusively from the quotes of Edvard Munch and his contemporaries. Filled with authenticity and life, Munch debunks the familiar myth of the half-mad expressionist painter - anguished, starving, and ill-treated - and draws out his neglected sense of humor and optimism. Born out of a lifelong fascination with Munch's life and work, this is a landmark of graphic biography and the funniest, most entertaining portrait yet of a complex man and the pioneering artist behind The Scream.
name: Vol. 3: Munch

description:
Chapter 10 of Avaiyo, Vol. 04

With only one task remaining, everything becomes that much more challenging. Complications erode their plan; it's the final act. Will this determine an outcome?
name: Enter Stage

description: Daniel has escaped his kidnappers' clutches! But now he and Bandette (the greatest thief in the world!) must not only survive the continued threat of Dart Petite's deadly missiles, but also rescue Daniel's fellow captives, find time to attend a parade (one must enjoy life, after all!) and also apprehend The Voice before that secretive villain uncovers... The House Of The Green Mask!
name: The House Of The Green Mask Part Four

story_arc_credits.name: The House of the Green Mask

first_appearance_storyarcs.name: The House of the Green Mask

description: When space pirates attack a convoy transporting the most powerful substance in the universe, Eton Langer is knocked out of the fight and into an adventure on an abandoned planet. Before long he finds himself fighting for both the life of the planet and his own! Now collected into a single volume, this science fiction saga by the writer of COLDER and PROMETHEUS is rich in scope and imagination, with just a side of snark. Contains bonus material not previously published.
name: TPB

description: Piano man down! Slim Watkins checks out behind “bug-juice”, just as Jimmy Watts, tenor sax avatar, has truly achieved sobriety. Could drummer Ralph Rojas have prevented Slim's demise? Maybe, but he's too busy with sexy Clarise, the leggy jazz fan with a penchant for boffing drummers.

Kevin Keene prepares for the ultimate role of his career; infiltrating the Cohort of Christ. Meanwhile, Grzzt, Maria Berenyi, Nate Josephson accompany the captured remains of the Kazoop tank to high level research facility.
name: The Spy Who Loved Me

description:
While on tour in Barcelona, Grace is imprisoned for the theft of a rather spectacular work of art, a unique creation by the great Master Salvador himself.

Rushing to her aid, Fourmille and Yuri attempt to clear her name... All the while trying to get Sigisbert, who they brought along, tied up and gagged in their luggage, to confess the secret of the Preshauns! But whilst the spirit of a cat sometimes occupies that of Fourmille, the city worries about the numerous disappearances of young girls...
name: Barcelona

description:
Among all the races of Elves, the Dark Elves are without a doubt the most troubling. Dark and silent killers, whether they are born Blue, White, Green, Red, or Grey, their real nature is only revealed after a few years...

Gaw'er is a young Blue Elf with a hot blood temperament, which has aroused the suspicions of his father... When his true nature is finally revealled, he is taken from his family, to be trained in the Citadel of Slurce, the Fortress of the Dark Elves. Gaw'yn, so baptized upon his arrival, then begins a long and painful apprenticeship to become a skillful and merciless killer, maybe the best among them...

But at night he hears a strange sound, an icy and terrifying noise that may spell doom for the young apprentice.
name: The Dynasty of the Dark Elves

description: When she was a little girl, passing her summers in the heat of coastal Australia, Evie Wyld was captivated by sharks - by their innate ruthlessness, stealth, and immeasurable power - and they have never released their hold on her imagination. From the award-winning author of All the Birds, Singing, here is a deeply moving graphic memoir about family, love, loss, and the irresistible forces that, like sharks, course through life unseen, ready to emerge at any moment.
name: GN

description:
For years the world was protected by the Power Society, a group of heroes who banded together to fight for all that was right. Then, in a shocking moment, they were gone--murdered in their own headquarters. But unbeknownst to the world, one of them survived--their young sidekick named JASON BRONZE aka THE GREEN OWL.

Now, nearly a decade after that horrible night, Jason continues the fight to take back his city and bring those that killed the Power Society to justice. But his one man war on crime is about to be joined by a new generation of heroes--including the son of one of the original Power Society members, a young man named DORIAN BLACK. Even as Jason introduces Dorian to the legacy of the crime-fighting "Owls", the duo must band together against an old threat--the SERIALS, some of Justice City's most notorious criminals that were believed long dead. And what is their link to the green, glowing liquid that seeps between the cracks of Justice streets? As the "Last Sidekick" and the new "Teen Owl" become fast friends and maybe more, a darkness looms over Justice City--one more threatening than ever before! The "Beacon of Justice" shines bright across the bay as shocking truths are about to be revealed in the all-new, reimagined OWLVERSE featuring GREEN OWL and HARROWING!
name: The Last Sidekick Part One

description: A famous manga artist provides the latest entry in the Louvre collection of graphic novels. After a group trip to Europe, a Japanese designer stops in Paris alone, intent on visiting the museums of the capital. But, bedridden in his hotel room with fever, he faces the absolute solitude of one suffering in a foreign land, deprived of any immediate or familiar recourse. When the fever breaks somewhat, he sets out on his visit and promptly gets lost in the crowded halls of the Louvre. Very soon, he discovers many unsuspected facets to this world in a museum, meeting artists and their works from various periods, in a journey oscillating between feverish hallucination and reality, finishing at the crossroads between human and personal history.
name: HC

description:
The curtain hits the cast on the debut of newly crowned Editor-in-Chief Grant Morrison's Heavy Metal debut! The legendary writer has plenty of surprises up his sleeve, with announcements to be rolled out in the weeks leading up to release of this landmark issue!

Grant's inaugural issue is a 140-page effort that includes seven comic stories from an international group of artists.

Grant Morrison opens up the issue with a tale he contributed himself, “an old school sci-fi twist-ender” entitled “Beachhead” drawn by Benjamin Marra, whim Morrison describes as a “grand guignol genius.” “Time Served” is a twisty sci-fi short by Kyle Charles and Michael Moreci. “The Key” is a hippy trippy mushroom headmelt, by Max Frezzato. In “Lepidoteran”, a jet pilot has a strange encounter, by Emilio Balcarce and Gaston Vivanco. Also--“A Mind Bomb” by Danish artist Anna Kornum. Morrison describes the story as “Raymond Briggs-y A-bomb paranoia.” "Fiendy" is a cerebral head crush by Gary T. Becks. “Magic Words” is a one pager by Eric Esquivel. Here you go! “Deliriously vivacious insect erotica,” writes Morrison of this story, an excerpt from Mozchops’ 2011 graphic novel "Salsa Invertebrexa". The “Artist's Studio” feature presents the work of Mimi Scholz, a Berlin-based artist whose work focuses on Feminism and sexuality. The magazine’s “Gallery” section, curated this issue by musician and art historian Tom Negovan, features a spotlight on Gail Potocki and "The Century Guild."

Continuing Julia and Roem by French comics master Enki Bilal. Also ongoing is The 49th Key by Erika Lewis, J.K. Woodward and Deron Bennetz.

Heavy Metal #280 has three different covers:

“Gringod” by contemporary Pop Art painter Ron English.

“Victory of the Dravenites” by Mozchops, a British conceptual painter and illustrator.

“Botanica No. 23” by Gail Potocki, a Symbolist painter whose work will also be featured in the magazine’s “Gallery” section, curated this issue by musician and art historian Tom Negovan.

description: Helen, Sweetheart of the Internet was the first comic strip to make the leap from the internet to newspaper syndication. It began online in 1996 and was syndicated to newspapers starting in 2000. Now ComicMix is reprinting her adventures from the very beginning! Helen Nichols - you know her, you love her, you fear her if you know what's good for you. Forget about those corporate suits upstairs in the corner office, because it's the techies who hold all the real business power today. It's a strange new world and nobody embodies the high-tech zeitgeist more thoroughly, more knowingly, or more hilariously, than Helen, "sweetheart of the internet." It's her universe, we just log into it.
name: Volume 1: 1996 - 1999

volume.name: Helen, Sweetheart of the Internet: Attack of the 50ft. Helen

description: Nothing is as it seems when the con artists of JACKPOT! are introduced to the hidden keys of the universe. But will any of them survive the mind-bending, reality-shattering result? Some of them are already starting to die...and return...

Meet the most intelligent person to ever live: an unpredictable maverick whose mind is his super power, with the ability to unlock universes we've only dreamed of. Try to keep up with his journeys through space, time, alternate dimensions and everything in between, as he explores the furthest reaches of our imagination. His ingenious inventions and creations are centuries ahead of their time - but is the world truly ready for Jonas Quantum?
name: TPB

volume.name: The Infinite Adventures of Jonas Quantum

description:
Josephine is plagued by misfortunes, but she is often her own worst enemy; she manages her professional relations and work poorly, struggles to be understood, is prone to blunders, and her love life is a succession of faux pas...

Fortunately, Josephine is divine... And divinely funny!
name: Vol. 1

description:
Josephine is plagued by misfortunes, but she is often her own worst enemy; she manages her professional relations and work poorly, struggles to be understood, is prone to blunders, and her love life is a succession of faux pas...

Fortunately, Josephine is divine... And divinely funny!
name: Not That Bad

description:
Josephine is plagued by misfortunes, but she is often her own worst enemy; she manages her professional relations and work poorly, struggles to be understood, is prone to blunders, and her love life is a succession of faux pas...

Fortunately, Josephine is divine... And divinely funny!
name: Switching Sides

description: Get ready for the all-new second season of Kaijumax! All the Red Humongo wants to do is go straight now that he's out on parole, but his good-for-nothing brother Green Humongo has escaped from Kaijumax and is crashing at his house, with fellow escapee Electrogor in tow. Out-of-work guard Jeong drinks his troubles away on the moon, while new police recruit Chisato throws herself enthusiastically into her first day on the job. Also: Blindside tackles! Filial piety! Savage beatings! And... a Flintstones reference?
name: Same Ambergris, Different Day

description: From critically acclaimed writer Joshua Hale Fialkov and superstar artists Bernard Chang and Marcelo Maiolo comes a post-apocalyptic Conan the Barbarian as directed by Sam Raimi circa Army of Darkness! King just wants what anybody wants: not to get fired, eaten, or forced to mate with a cheetah lady. As Earth's sole human survivor after the apocalypse, life among Los Angeles' strange, new populace ain't easy. Working for the LA Department of Reclamation, King gets a lot of crappy jobs going on quests and searching for artifacts from the "old world." The work commute can be a real pain in the Azathoth. The 405 freeway is filled with mutants, monsters, mayhem and tentacled Elder Gods. And that's all before you hit the horrors of the San Fernando Valley. As the world's freakish inhabitants battle for supremacy, King searches for the "seed of life," which may give Earth the second chance it probably doesn't even deserve.
name: TPB

description: John Porcellino's beloved and long-running autobiographical series celebrates its 25th Anniversary with this moving tribute to his cat Maisie Kukoc. This standalone issue is a perfect read for fans of the autobio genre, pet lovers, or simply those looking for a genuine, thoughtful story. A 2015 Ignatz Award Nominee for Outstanding Minicomic.

There's nothing like a pleasure cruise... and this issue is nothing like a pleasure cruise! Traveling upriver through a series of rapids, Mammoth faces off against a revenge-seeking Liam Valorous. Did we mention he's sparring on the stern (how nautical!) of a moving boats? Or that he only has one arm? Adventure on the high, er, river has never been this desperate -- or deadly!

Lady Death is a fierce symbol of power, but even the diva of death has a naughty nature. Feast your eyes on fantastic imagery depicting Lady Death's sensual side by today's top illustrators with this 48 page, 9" x 12" limited edition hardcover art book! Features artwork by Richard Ortiz, Mike DeBalfo, Dawn McTeigue, Paolo Pantalena, Sabine Rich, Nei Ruffino, Monte Moore, Eric Basaldua (Ebas) and many more! Hand picked and art directed by Lady Death creator Brian Pulido, the standard edition is limited to 2,000 copies. Also available is an edition signed by Pulido and bagged with an art print, limited to 250 copies.

Lou is an 11 year old tomboy growing up in a small, working-class town in New England in the 1990s. This one summer it becomes clear that her brother Eddie's boss at the pizza shop is mixed up in some unsavory business. Things become more precarious after Eddie's boss vanishes.
name: GN

description: In Monsters Among Us urban legends are very real. Billionaire Solomon Kane believes God has charged his family to rid of the world of mythical creatures. A mysterious crew comprised of gentle beasts including Bigfoot, a Chupacabra, and the Mothman must unite and fight to survive. Written by THE AMAZING RACE star Andrew Shayde.

The boundless adventures of an unruly boy, his rational robot and their great gadgets filled with fantastic science stuff! Plus Man is a roguish knave without equal, an antihero in his own mind. His level-headed robot, however, knows better. This odd couple has just been given a break: a tip on a score of valuable alloy. The catch? The alloy is in a haunted castle. One really haunted castle. Like a young Indiana Jones with super science, Plus Man successfully bumbles his way through hair-raising heists and sticky situations.
name: GN

description: What happens when the virtual world you dedicated your life to gets unplugged and ripped away? PLOX tells the story of Chad, the raid leader with no patience, Roy, the rational one that would rather play with dice and paper, and Kim, the guild leader at the end of her rope. Set in Columbus, Ohio where three people, bound by World of Warcraft, Dungeons & Dragons, and friendship, try to level up in their real lives. When the games we play forge our identity, hell is other players.
name: GN

description: Now in possession of the world’s deadliest weapon, and with the entire United States Government searching for him, Matthew does what any ten-year-old boy would do. He plays with it! But he soon learns that with great power come great, and sometimes deadly, consequences.

Fate has chosen Raman Lamba to be the Reincarnation Man and gifted him with the ability to draw great heroes from the past to save the present. In this final explosive issue Raman fights to save all of creation from being corrupted by the forces of evil that aim to break the cycle of life itself!

In Rules for Dating My Daughter, Mike Dawson uses visual storytelling to offer original, compelling, and funny commentary on fatherhood, gun rights, the gender of toys, and staying sane in a world where school shootings and Disney princesses get equal billing. Rules is the perfect guide to today's vexing mediascape.
name: GN
